  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We present the threshold N$^3$LO perturbative QCD corrections to the rapidity distributions of di-leptons in the Drell-Yan and of Higgs boson in gluon fusion. Sudakov resummation of QCD amplitudes, renormalization group invariance and the mass factorization theorem provide useful guidelines to obtain them in an elegant manner. We have used various state of the art three loop results that have been recently available to obtain these distributions. For Higgs boson, we demonstrate numerically the importance of these corrections at the LHC.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
  </datafield>
